Explanation:

- The DELETE /admin/media/{media} route is handled by App\Http\Controllers\Admin\MediaLibraryController::destroy(Media $medium).
- The controller uses Laravel route-model binding to resolve the {media} path parameter into a Media model instance (App\Models\Media).
- The destroy method calls $medium->delete() then returns a RedirectResponse redirecting to the admin.media.index route with a success flash message. Thus a successful request yields an HTTP redirect (302) rather than a JSON body.
- If route-model binding fails (no matching Media), Laravel would return a 404 Not Found.
- The path parameter {media} corresponds to the Media model primary key. The Media model extends Spatie's BaseMedia which uses an integer id by default, so the path parameter is modeled as an integer.

Based on only the information in the code, the Operation Object includes summary, description, the path parameter definition, and responses for the successful redirect (302) and not-found (404).

